select count(*) as aggregate from `countries` where (`name` like '%%')

select `countries`.*, (select count(*) from `restaurants` inner join `zones` on `zones`.`id` = `restaurants`.`zone_id` where `countries`.`id` = `zones`.`country_id`) as `restaurants_count`, (select count(*) from `delivery_men` inner join `zones` on `zones`.`id` = `delivery_men`.`zone_id` where `countries`.`id` = `zones`.`country_id`) as `deliverymen_count` from `countries` where (`name` like '%%') order by `created_at` desc limit 25 offset 0
select count(*) as aggregate from `conversations` where (`sender_type` = 'admin' or `receiver_type` = 'admin') and `unread_message_count` > '0'
select count(*) as aggregate from `orders` where `order_status` = 'pending'

select COUNT(*) as total,
COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status = "delivered" THEN 1 END) as delivered,
COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status = "canceled" THEN 1 END) as canceled,
COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status = "failed" THEN 1 END) as failed,
COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status = "refunded" THEN 1 END) as refunded,
COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status = "refund_requested" THEN 1 END) as refund_requested,
COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status IN ("confirmed", "processing","handover") THEN 1 END) as processing,
COUNT(CASE WHEN created_at <> schedule_at AND scheduled = 1 THEN 1 END) as scheduled from `orders` where `order_type` <> 'pos' and ((exists (select * from `subscriptions` where `orders`.`subscription_id` = `subscriptions`.`id` and `status` = 'active' and date(`start_at`) <= '2024-06-27' and date(`end_at`) >= '2024-06-27' and exists (select * from `subscription_schedules` where `subscriptions`.`id` = `subscription_schedules`.`subscription_id` and ((`type` = 'weekly' and `day` = 4) or (`type` = 'monthly' and `day` = 27) or `type` = 'daily')) and not exists (select * from `subscription_pauses` where `subscriptions`.`id` = `subscription_pauses`.`subscription_id` and date(`from`) <= '2024-06-27' and date(`to`) >= '2024-06-27')) and not exists (select * from `subscription_logs` where `orders`.`id` = `subscription_logs`.`order_id` and (date(`schedule_at`) = '2024-06-27' or `order_status` in ('delivered', 'failed', 'canceled', 'refund_requested', 'refund_request_canceled', 'refunded')))) or `subscription_id` is null) limit 1

select COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status = "pending" THEN 1 END) as pending,
COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status = "picked_up" THEN 1 END) as picked_up,
COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status IN ("accepted", "confirmed","processing","handover","picked_up") THEN 1 END) as ongoing,
COUNT(CASE WHEN delivery_man_id IS NULL  AND order_type = "delivery" AND order_status NOT IN ("delivered", "failed","canceled","refund_requested","refund_request_canceled","refunded") THEN 1 END) as searching_dm,
COUNT(CASE WHEN order_status = "accepted" THEN 1 END) as accepted from `orders` where `order_type` <> 'pos' and ((exists (select * from `subscriptions` where `orders`.`subscription_id` = `subscriptions`.`id` and `status` = 'active' and date(`start_at`) <= '2024-06-27' and date(`end_at`) >= '2024-06-27' and exists (select * from `subscription_schedules` where `subscriptions`.`id` = `subscription_schedules`.`subscription_id` and ((`type` = 'weekly' and `day` = 4) or (`type` = 'monthly' and `day` = 27) or `type` = 'daily')) and not exists (select * from `subscription_pauses` where `subscriptions`.`id` = `subscription_pauses`.`subscription_id` and date(`from`) <= '2024-06-27' and date(`to`) >= '2024-06-27')) and not exists (select * from `subscription_logs` where `orders`.`id` = `subscription_logs`.`order_id` and (date(`schedule_at`) = '2024-06-27' or `order_status` in ('delivered', 'failed', 'canceled', 'refund_requested', 'refund_request_canceled', 'refunded')))) or `subscription_id` is null) and ((created_at <> schedule_at and (`schedule_at` between '2024-06-27 03:26:28' and '2024-06-27 03:56:28') or `schedule_at` < '2024-06-27 03:26:28') or created_at = schedule_at) limit 1
select count(*) as aggregate from `orders` where exists (select * from `offline_payments` where `orders`.`id` = `offline_payments`.`order_id`) and `order_type` <> 'pos'
select count(*) as aggregate from `disbursements` where `created_for` = 'restaurant'
select count(*) as aggregate from `disbursements` where `created_for` = 'delivery_man'
